    <div class="well" style="width: 100%; height:400px">
      <pubtit>Axion Quasiparticles for Axion Dark Matter Detection</pubtit>
      <p><img src="http://localhost:4000/images/pubpic/2102.05366.png" class="img-responsive" width="33%" style="float: left" /></p>
      <p>The axion quasiparticles is a longitudinal antiferromagnetic spin fluctuation which mixes with the photon when an external magnetic field is applied. This mixing provides the photon with a tuneable mass, allowing for resonant conversion of axion dark matter into THz photons in a material volume that is independent of the resonant frequency. We develop a formalism for providing a realistic sensitivity estimate for an experiment…</p>
      <p><em>Jan Schütte-Engel, David J. E. Marsh, Alexander J. Millar, Akihiko Sekine, Francesca Chadha-Day, Sebastian Hoof, Mazhar Ali, Kin-Chung Fong, Edward Hardy, Libor Šmejkal</em></p>
      <p><strong><a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2102.05366">https://arxiv.org/abs/2102.05366</a></strong></p>
      <p class="text-danger"><strong> </strong></p>
      <p> </p>
    </div>
